The paper proposes a method for classifying motor imagery tasks using EEG signals and a convolutional neural network. This falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE) as it involves the decoding of brain signals. The use of a neural network also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves image processing techniques such as convolution, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the study involves the potential application of the proposed method in rehabilitation and recovery, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
